        <p class="metadata">Posted by Matthew Weier O'Phinney (matthew) on 2008-12-30T08:50:01.000+0000</p> 
        <div class="body">
            <p>Reflection is built-in to PHP by default -- you must actually explicitly disable it at compile time if you do not want it. A number of ZF components utilize it, and we consider it a standard dependency of the framework.</p>

<p>Moreover, its use here is a good one in terms of maintainability, as it ensures that the constants and priorities stay in sync.</p>

